In a statement, Sars customs officials say two female suspects were arrested and have been handed over to the police. JOHANNESBURG - South African Revenue Service (Sars) customs officials have confiscated cocaine valued at an estimated R3.6 million in two separate incidents at the OR Tambo International Airport this week.Both parcels were intercepted when officials searched flights from South America.In the first incident, drugs weighing 1,7kg were found in hidden compartments inside three new bags.In the second interception, ten canned fruit tins weighing 6,8kg tested positive for cocaine and the owner of the bags, a female traveller, was handcuffed.In a statement, the service says two female suspects were arrested in both cases and have been handed over to the police.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)